NIGHT/SHIFT: A Cypherpunk Adventure

2039: In the afflicted city of Boston, three young citizens uncover the 
greatest conspiracy of their time.

A thoughtful and inspiring fusion of dystopia and nostalgia in an 
Amiga-exclusive exploration game.

For screenshots, please visit https://www.nightshift.cx

Technical features:

* Hi-Res HAM8 graphics
* 70 visitable / explorable locations
* OS-friendly implementation:
    * multitasking-capable
    * screen-draggable
* Optimized for widescreen display
    
System requirements:

* Amiga with AGA (or SAGA) chipset
* 2 MB Chip RAM
* AmigaOS 3.x
* 23 MB free harddisk space
* PAL output

Installation instructions:

Extract the "NightShift.lha" archive into any harddisk folder and launch 
the game via the "NightShift" icon.

Gameplay instructions:

* This is an easy-to-play adventure game without hard puzzles or dead ends
* The game is played with just the mouse (only one button required)
* By clicking on Sean (top left corner), the current state can be saved
* A saved game can be resumed from the title menu ("Start" / "Resume")
* A slighty different outcome at the very end can be achieved when
    * playing through the entire game in one go and/or
    * impressing Lisa with humor, compliments and determination

This game has been developed on Apollo V4 Standalone with AmiBlitz3.

